Introduction

Weeekly is a six-member girl group.

On October 18, 2018, FAVE Entertainment announced their plans to debut a new girl group in the first quarter of 2019. The group, then known as FAVEGIRLS, revealed seven trainees, starting October 21 with Lee Soojin, followed by Monday on October 22, Park Haelin on October 23, Shin Jiyoon on October 24, Park Soeun on October 25, Kim Gaeun on October 26, and finally, Lee Jaehee on October 27. Among them, Lee Soojin, Shin Jiyoon, and Park Soeun were already known for their participation in the survival show MIXNINE.

Due to FAVE Entertainment and Play M Entertainment merging in early 2019, the group's name was changed to PlayM GIRLS, and their debut was delayed.

In July and August 2019, it was announced that trainees Park Haelin and Kim Gaeun had left the agency and the group. Two months later, in October, Han Jihyo and Cho Hyewon were added to the lineup. It was later revealed that the two would uses stage name, Jihan and Zoa respectively, throught a video uploaded on their official YouTube channel on April 28, 2020, titled 'Who R U?'.

Their group name, 'Weeekly' was announced on May 11, 2020, along with the seven members being officially confirmed. The group debuted on June 30, 2020, with the release of their first mini album, "We Are", and its title track "Tag Me (@Me)".

On August 23, 2020, Weeekly's fandom name was announced to be "Daileee", taken from the word "Daily", and meaning "without Daileee, Weeekly cannot exist."

On August 1, 2021, Jiyoon first hiatus was announced by Play M Entertainment, with the reason being health issues and, more precisely, reoccurring stress and anxiety. She returned to the group on December 15, 2021 but, on February 28, 2022, it was reported that she would go on a second hiatus to focus on her recovery for her anxiety. Later that year, on June 1, 2022, IST Entertainment announced that Jiyoon would be leaving the group due to her health issues, and that Weeekly would continue to promote as a six-member group from now on.

After Jiyoon's departure, the group wasn't much active for more than a year, even having four out of six members (Lee Soojin, Park Soeun, Jihan, and Zoa) participating in Queendom Puzzle, and didn't make music until September 4, 2023, when they released the digital single "Good Day (Special Daileee)", their first release as six.

On February 26, 2025, it was reported that all the members of Weeekly had left IST Entertainment. However, no official informations about the group's state was announced yet, leaving it unclear if they disbanded or if they will continue to do promotions.
